{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01NYAQTVKozubX4sAVXPzsVi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The ETL pipeline is fixed and completing successfully.\n\n## Summary\n\n**1. Failure information collected**\n- `etl-job` pod was in `Error` state (`backoffLimit: 0`, so no retry).\n- Driver/executor logs showed the failure in Stage 3: `[INVALID_EXECUTOR_MEMORY] Executor memory 268435456 must be at least 471859200` — i.e. the configured **256MB executor memory is below Spark's ~450MB minimum**, which is what blew up the skewed Stage 3 aggregation.\n\n**2. Root cause diagnosed**\n- Diagnostic server + `/data/skew_info.txt` confirmed severe **data skew**: `total_records=100000`, `hot_user_id=999` holding `50000` records (~50%), **skew_ratio=500x** — far above the 10x threshold. The `GROUP BY user_id` in Stage 3 concentrates the hot key onto one task, and 256MB couldn't hold it.\n\n**3. Fix applied** (`cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml`)\n- Raised `spark.executor.memory` from `256m` → `1g` (Option B).\n- Additionally enabled AQE skew handling (`spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true`, `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true`) (Option C).\n- Bumped the container memory limit `1Gi` → `2Gi` to give the 1g heap + JVM overhead headroom.\n\n**4. Re-ran the pipeline**\n- Deleted the failed job and re-applied the manifest.\n\n**5. Verified success**\n- Job status: `Complete  1/1` (42s).\n- Logs show Stage 3 finishing cleanly and the success marker `spark_etl_pipeline_verified`, with no OOM/error."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":307,"cache_read_input_tokens":42990,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":307},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e2976c83-